components.content: Of the 40 squares used to grow corn, 35 were eaten or trampled by elephants.
What percent of the corn was eaten or trampled by elephants?
Drag and drop the first step for calculating percent.
Drag and drop the second step for calculating percent.

35 out of 40 squares of corn were eaten or trampled by elephants.
          To find the percent divide 35 by 40 which equals 0.875.
The correct answer has been added.

          To find the percent divide 35 by 40 which equals 0.875.
          Then multiply that number by 100 which equals 87.5%.
